#. type: Title =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using `TargetSource` Implementations"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:9
msgid ""
"Spring offers the concept of a `TargetSource`, expressed in the "
"`org.springframework.aop.TargetSource` interface. This interface is "
"responsible for returning the \"`target object`\" that implements the join "
"point. The `TargetSource` implementation is asked for a target instance each "
"time the AOP proxy handles a method invocation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:14
msgid ""
"Developers who use Spring AOP do not normally need to work directly with "
"`TargetSource` implementations, but this provides a powerful means of "
"supporting pooling, hot swappable, and other sophisticated targets. For "
"example, a pooling `TargetSource` can return a different target instance for "
"each invocation, by using a pool to manage instances."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:17
msgid ""
"If you do not specify a `TargetSource`, a default implementation is used to "
"wrap a local object. The same target is returned for each invocation (as you "
"would expect)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:19
msgid ""
"The rest of this section describes the standard target sources provided with "
"Spring and how you can use them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:23
msgid ""
"When using a custom target source, your target will usually need to be a "
"prototype rather than a singleton bean definition. This allows Spring to "
"create a new target instance when required."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "Hot-swappable Target Sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:30
msgid ""
"The `org.springframework.aop.target.HotSwappableTargetSource` exists to let "
"the target of an AOP proxy be switched while letting callers keep their "
"references to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Changing the target source's target takes effect immediately. The "
"`HotSwappableTargetSource` is thread-safe."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:35
msgid ""
"You can change the target by using the `swap()` method on "
"HotSwappableTargetSource, as the follow example shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:38
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:149
#, no-wrap
msgid "Java"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tHotSwappableTargetSource swapper = (HotSwappableTargetSource) "
"beanFactory.getBean(\"swapper\");\n"
"\tObject oldTarget = swapper.swap(newTarget);\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:46
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:157
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kotlin"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tval swapper = beanFactory.getBean(\"swapper\") as "
"HotSwappableTargetSource\n"
"\tval oldTarget = swapper.swap(newTarget)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:56
msgid "The following example shows the required XML definitions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "\t<bean id=\"initialTarget\" class=\"mycompany.OldTarget\"/>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"swapper\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.target.HotSwappableTargetSource\">\n"
"\t\t<constructor-arg ref=\"initialTarget\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"swappable\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.framework.ProxyFactoryBean\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetSource\" ref=\"swapper\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:73
msgid ""
"The preceding `swap()` call changes the target of the swappable "
"bean. Clients that hold a reference to that bean are unaware of the change "
"but immediately start hitting the new target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:77
msgid ""
"Although this example does not add any advice (it is not necessary to add "
"advice to use a `TargetSource`), any `TargetSource` can be used in "
"conjunction with arbitrary advice."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pooling Target Sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:85
msgid ""
"Using a pooling target source provides a similar programming model to "
"stateless session EJBs, in which a pool of identical instances is "
"maintained, with method invocations going to free objects in the pool."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:89
msgid ""
"A crucial difference between Spring pooling and SLSB pooling is that Spring "
"pooling can be applied to any POJO. As with Spring in general, this service "
"can be applied in a non-invasive way."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:95
msgid ""
"Spring provides support for Commons Pool 2, which provides a fairly "
"efficient pooling implementation. You need the `commons-pool` Jar on your "
"application's classpath to use this feature. You can also subclass "
"`org.springframework.aop.target.AbstractPoolingTargetSource` to support any "
"other pooling API."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:97
msgid "The following listing shows an example configuration:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:104
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"businessObjectTarget\" "
"class=\"com.mycompany.MyBusinessObject\"\n"
"\t\t\tscope=\"prototype\">\n"
"\t\t... properties omitted\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:109
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"poolTargetSource\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.target.CommonsPool2TargetSource\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetBeanName\" value=\"businessObjectTarget\"/>\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"maxSize\" value=\"25\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"businessObject\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.framework.ProxyFactoryBean\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetSource\" ref=\"poolTargetSource\"/>\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"interceptorNames\" value=\"myInterceptor\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:121
msgid ""
"Note that the target object (`businessObjectTarget` in the preceding "
"example) must be a prototype. This lets the `PoolingTargetSource` "
"implementation create new instances of the target to grow the pool as "
"necessary. See the "
"{spring-framework-api}/aop/target/AbstractPoolingTargetSource.html[javadoc "
"of `AbstractPoolingTargetSource`] and the concrete subclass you wish to use "
"for information about its properties. `maxSize` is the most basic and is "
"always guaranteed to be present."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:126
msgid ""
"In this case, `myInterceptor` is the name of an interceptor that would need "
"to be defined in the same IoC context. However, you need not specify "
"interceptors to use pooling. If you want only pooling and no other advice, "
"do not set the `interceptorNames` property at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:131
msgid ""
"You can configure Spring to be able to cast any pooled object to the "
"`org.springframework.aop.target.PoolingConfig` interface, which exposes "
"information about the configuration and current size of the pool through an "
"introduction. You need to define an advisor similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"poolConfigAdvisor\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.beans.factory.config.MethodInvokingFactoryBean\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetObject\" ref=\"poolTargetSource\"/>\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetMethod\" value=\"getPoolingConfigMixin\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:144
msgid ""
"This advisor is obtained by calling a convenience method on the "
"`AbstractPoolingTargetSource` class, hence the use of "
"`MethodInvokingFactoryBean`. This advisor's name (`poolConfigAdvisor`, here) "
"must be in the list of interceptors names in the `ProxyFactoryBean` that "
"exposes the pooled object."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:146
msgid "The cast is defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tPoolingConfig conf = (PoolingConfig) "
"beanFactory.getBean(\"businessObject\");\n"
"\tSystem.out.println(\"Max pool size is \" + conf.getMaxSize());\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tval conf = beanFactory.getBean(\"businessObject\") as PoolingConfig\n"
"\tprintln(\"Max pool size is \" + conf.maxSize)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:169
msgid ""
"Pooling stateless service objects is not usually necessary. We do not "
"believe it should be the default choice, as most stateless objects are "
"naturally thread-safe, and instance pooling is problematic if resources are "
"cached."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:172
msgid ""
"Simpler pooling is available by using auto-proxying. You can set the "
"`TargetSource` implementations used by any auto-proxy creator."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:175
#, no-wrap
msgid "Prototype Target Sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:182
msgid ""
"Setting up a \"`prototype`\" target source is similar to setting up a "
"pooling `TargetSource`. In this case, a new instance of the target is "
"created on every method invocation. Although the cost of creating a new "
"object is not high in a modern JVM, the cost of wiring up the new object "
"(satisfying its IoC dependencies) may be more expensive. Thus, you should "
"not use this approach without very good reason."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:185
msgid ""
"To do this, you could modify the `poolTargetSource` definition shown earlier "
"as follows (we also changed the name, for clarity):"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:191
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"prototypeTargetSource\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.target.PrototypeTargetSource\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetBeanName\" ref=\"businessObjectTarget\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:196
msgid ""
"The only property is the name of the target bean. Inheritance is used in the "
"`TargetSource` implementations to ensure consistent naming. As with the "
"pooling target source, the target bean must be a prototype bean definition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "`ThreadLocal` Target Sources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:206
msgid ""
"`ThreadLocal` target sources are useful if you need an object to be created "
"for each incoming request (per thread that is). The concept of a "
"`ThreadLocal` provides a JDK-wide facility to transparently store a resource "
"alongside a thread. Setting up a `ThreadLocalTargetSource` is pretty much "
"the same as was explained for the other types of target source, as the "
"following example shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:212
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"threadlocalTargetSource\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.aop.target.ThreadLocalTargetSource\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"targetBeanName\" value=\"businessObjectTarget\"/>\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/aop-api/targetsource.adoc:222
msgid ""
"`ThreadLocal` instances come with serious issues (potentially resulting in "
"memory leaks) when incorrectly using them in multi-threaded and "
"multi-classloader environments. You should always consider wrapping a "
"`ThreadLocal` in some other class and never directly use the `ThreadLocal` "
"itself (except in the wrapper class). Also, you should always remember to "
"correctly set and unset (where the latter involves a call to "
"`ThreadLocal.remove()`) the resource local to the thread. Unsetting should "
"be done in any case, since not unsetting it might result in problematic "
"behavior. Spring's `ThreadLocal` support does this for you and should always "
"be considered in favor of using `ThreadLocal` instances without other proper "
"handling code."
msgstr ""
